title: Prep roundup: Evergreens sweep Memorial
text:
Prep roundup: Evergreens sweep Memorial Daily Herald Media 10:42 p.m. CDT October 19, 2015 The University of Wisconsin Marathon County volleyball team captured the Wisconsin Collegiate Conference title for the second straight year this past weekend in Wisconsin Dells. (Photo: Photo courtesy of Hannah Brabec) 13 CONNECT TWEET LINKEDIN COMMENT EMAIL MORE 
EAU CLAIRE — Natalie Mohring had 29 assists, 17 digs and three aces as the D.C. Everest volleyball team swept Eau Claire Memorial in its final match of the regular season Monday. 
Scores in the nonconference game were 27-25, 25-14, 29-27. 
Alyssa Frahm had 20 digs to lead the Evergreens, while Regan Stefan had a team-high 23 kills. 
Jenna Rombalski added 16 digs and 14 kills, while Caroline Hehir chipped in with 13 assists. 
Hehir and Amanda Brown also had three aces. 
The Evergreens are seeded second in Division 1 in the WIAA playoffs and host either Stevens Point Area Senior High or Chippewa Falls in a regional title game Saturday. 
LATE SATURDAY 
WCC tournament 
WISCONSIN DELLS — Hanna Doughty and Morgan Wirkus both earned all-tournament honors as the University of Wisconsin Marathon County won the Wisconsin Collegiate Conference championship. 
The Huskies defeated UW-Waukesha 28-26, 25-22 in the title game to win the conference tournament for the second straight year. 13 CONNECT TWEET LINKEDIN COMMENT EMAIL MORE Read or Share this story: http://wdhne.ws/1LHwo38 TOP VIDEOS
